<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/331981-lisa"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1580272405i/331981._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/331981-lisa">Lisa</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    All that Nick saw was Toby approaching the car in the headlights (like a wild animal) and then he saw him kissing Michael (even though it was Michael <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    All that Nick saw was Toby approaching the car in the headlights (like a wild animal) and then he saw him kissing Michael (even though it was Michael who had initiated it). Nick wouldn’t have seen Michael’s thoughts - all he saw was Toby approaching Michael. Nick probably really thought Toby was gone crazy, first kissing Michael, then kissing Dora. That is exactly what he accused him of. He may have been disgusted by Toby. Either way, Nick acted like a jerk. He was always drunk and angry or sarcastic. Nick came to the court because he was living a debauched life, possibly with nowhere to live and nowhere to turn, dropped out of every enterprise in which he may have made something of himself. It was all an extenuation of his “trouble-maker” character from his school days. His sister was trying to rescue him so she begged a place for him at the court, hoping he might find encouragement. There is no evidence that Nick had sought to come to the court on his own. Nick had never been in love with Michael, as can be seen from his alternating treatment of Michael - always disregard or disdain. Only his twin sister (who had dressed up like him back in school - maybe to cover for him while he went off and partied or was in danger of dropping out - like he did Oxford and his engineering program? Or did they switch just as a joke?- like Dora’s bell switch joke at the end of the story). This story has so many misunderstandings in it it is crazy! Nick probably committed suicide when he realized that his trick with making the new bell fall into the water caused Catherine to lose her nerve, almost drown herself, and then be committed to a mental institution. He had been callous and depressed before, but the realization that his actions almost killed his sister pushed him over the edge emotionally to commit suicide. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
