<div id="review_189886412" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/189886412" />
    <a title="Robert" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2744544-robert"><img alt="Robert" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465764198p2/2744544.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/189886412?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert" href="/user/show/2744544-robert">Robert</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099283898" href="/book/show/1193744.The_Bell">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer189886412" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14439767115324440835">I really don&apos;t know why so many people like The Bell when Murdoch has written better books? I find the Bell cumbersome and lacking soul. Sure the characters are ok, but Murdoch became better at creating fully fledged people AND mixed in philosophy at the same time. <br/><br/>The story is about a group of rather nasty people who go on a retreat at an abbey but are entangled in each other&apos;s lives with the bell being the focal part of their lives and possibly their redemption from being materialistic and hav</span>
  <span id="freeText14439767115324440835" style="display:none">I really don't know why so many people like The Bell when Murdoch has written better books? I find the Bell cumbersome and lacking soul. Sure the characters are ok, but Murdoch became better at creating fully fledged people AND mixed in philosophy at the same time. <br /><br />The story is about a group of rather nasty people who go on a retreat at an abbey but are entangled in each other's lives with the bell being the focal part of their lives and possibly their redemption from being materialistic and having impure thoughts. It's clunky in places but I guess it is the signpost to what Murdoch would do over the next 3 decades.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14439767115324440835" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


